[COLOR dodgerblue][B]Version 7.2.7[/B][/COLOR]
- New "Skip Intro/Outro" feature: a Netflix-style Skip button appears during episode playback to jump past intros, recaps, and outros.
- Skip timings come from crowd-sourced IntroDB data, with AniSkip used for anime episodes and an optional chapter-based fallback.
- Configure under Settings > Playback: enable it, toggle AniSkip, and tune minimum confidence/submissions and button duration (off by default).
- Skip-marker data is cached and can be cleared from the maintenance menu ("Clear Skip Markers Cache").
- Stability fix: reworked the "In Progress" home widget to reduce a thread race that could crash Kodi.


[COLOR dodgerblue][B]Version 7.2.6[/B][/COLOR]
- New "Quick Add" context-menu item: one tap adds or removes the highlighted movie/show from a single chosen list.
- Pick your Quick Add target in Settings > Context Menu: Trakt Watchlist, TMDb Watchlist/Favorites, Finder Favorites, or any of your Trakt/TMDb/Finder personal lists.
- The menu entry reads "Add to ..." or "Remove from ..." depending on whether the item is already in that list.
- When no target is set, it falls back to your Trakt Watchlist (or Finder Favorites if Trakt isn't connected).


